    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="562"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Food Administrator’s File</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Food Administrator</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hoover</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Food Administration Representative at
                        London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLP1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sheldon</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The exportable balance of wheat from United States is now only 33,000,000 bushels
                    disregarding conservation and from Canada 100,000,000 bushels. As Allied needs
                    are over 40,000,000 bushels for month it is absolutely imperative that
                    arrangements be made to purchase and load Argentine grain at the earliest
                    possible moment. It seems to me vital that in order for them to purchase
                    Argentine freely and at reasonable prices at the earliest possible moment
                    arrangements should be made to positively limit neutral bunkers to announce this
                    policy. Altogether I suggest you meet with Wheat Executive<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d562fn1">See footnote 1, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_653">p. 653</ref>.</note> in London and discuss whole matter
                    fully.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
